Introduction

Hi-L was a six-member girl group under Kpop Live Entertainment. Their name stands for High Insight Libre. They made their official debut on August 11, 2021 with their first mini album Go High with the title track "Too Too (22)".

The members consisted of Yerin, Soojung (left in January 16, 2023), Dakyung, Joo A, Hayun, and Ye Seul (now in upcoming girl group LURA LUCY).

They presumably disbanded sometime in 2023.
